This is a compiled copy of TSF:SoTV as it stands right now, no new chapters as of yet, that should change by the end of the week..but of course if you haven't been looking in the Fan Fic boards then 2 of these will be new. Either way Enjoy  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><BR>---------------------<P><BR>                        -----------------------<P>                        For almost 500 years , I have watched Norrath changed, blossom and decay. Nations rise and fall...teachings are<BR>                        learned and forgotten. Unfortunately the latter happened to what my beloved tried to show to the world. The truth<BR>                        behind all things fell upon deaf ears...the 'gods' sway has gone undiminished...but like all things. They changed. Through<BR>                        our offspring, the truth is starting to be spread once again. Maybe this generation can finally convince Norrath...or<BR>                        maybe it will fall tot eh wayside once again..maybe...regardless of what happens, the winds of change are blowing was<BR>                        once again and Norrath will never be the same.<BR>                        --------------------<P>                        Kyt hated the underground caverns, they stunk like the pits of hell and were as dark as pitch.<P>                        |Why don't they ever clean these damn caverns?|<P>                        I have no idea Mika. You would think they would a city, A capital city, no less as rich as Palsa could pay some one to<BR>                        clean it.<P>                        |Beauracrats..|<P>                        No kidding <P>                        |Kyt..slow down a bit, I don't like this he has to be around here somewhere.|<P>                        Can't you sense his familiar?<P>                        |No..That scares me...I should be able to sense familiars|<P>                        I hate to admit it, but this is scaring me too..I almost wish that I had waited a bit..|<P>                        |Big bad Kyt? scared? I'm shocked. Don't worry, You will do just fine, your more then ready to become th- DUCK!!!!|<P>                        Kyt ducked at her familiar’s advice just a chain shot out of the shadows and sailed over her. She then rolled to the<BR>                        right, withdrawing her scimitar. A blue wolf appeared behind her running at high speed, it leapt and just as it was about<BR>                        to land on her back, it shimmered and in a flash of darkness, it was gone, and upon Kyt was suit of blue spiked armor.<P>                        Her breath drew short, as her eyes darted from side to side, trying to pierce the darkness searching for her target. <P>                        |Calm down, Kyt, if your heart starts beating any faster and harder, you'll rattle off your armor.|<P>                        You would like that wouldn't you?<P>                        | I refrain to answer that..it might incriminate me..|<P>                        She smiled, but the smile faded as she noticed her that her breath was becoming visible, the mist hanging in the air<BR>                        because of the cold.<P>                        He's close.<P>                        |Your armor is rattling...|<P>                        I'm scared.......I'm not ready for this!!!!<P>                        "Too late to run now" Spoke a deep voice behind her. She wheeled around, swinging her scimitar at the voice, it<BR>                        exploded as it touched a fiery red cloak. She gasped then cried out, as two chains arced out of the shadows and<BR>                        collided with her armor, shattering the familiar armor, leaving her in nothing but her burlap under clothing. Another flash<BR>                        of darkness went off, catapulting her backwards flying through the air.<P>                        |KYT!!!|<P>                        Four more chains harpooned out the darkness, each of the chains buried themselves into her wrists and ankles, then<BR>                        hoisted her up off the ground, spread eagling her.<P>                        A cold, deep voice laugh crept out of the darkness, a tall shape stepped out. The majority of the figure couldn't be<BR>                        made out by the pain wracked girl, but she could very clearing make out the fiery cape and cowl.<P>                        Mika....Help me!!!!!<P>                        The blue wolf, appearing at her side, charged the tall figure. The wolf leapt it's teeth bared, and was shredded by a<BR>                        barrage of chains through it's body. The mutilated body crashed tot he ground, just barely alive.<P>                        |Kyt...I'm sorry.....I've failed y-|<P>                        The wolf howled as it exploded into flames.<P>                        MIKA! Mika!! Answer me!!!!!!!!! Say something!!!!!!!!!!<P>                        The figure laughed again. <P>                        "Your familiar is gone girl, as you will be. But you will not be so fortunate as it. I intend on savoring your soul."<P>                        "YOU..bas... I'll kill you!!!"<P>                        The figure responded with several lashes from his shadow chains, they bit into her flesh making her scream in pain.<BR>                        Another barrage tore off some of her flesh and what little clothing she had left on.<P>                        The figure smiled. He moved up to her, and with his hand clutched her face. <P>                        "Such beauty.I shall savor every moment of ecstasy, every second of exquisite pain." to make his point, the chains<BR>                        began to retract slowly.<P>                        She screamed and then spat into his face. "Do you what want!! You and I both know that you aren't a true Hell Lord!!<BR>                        You may have beaten me!! But you will always be a Mal'shak!! You never could claim the title!!! You could never beat -"<P>                        The figure's eyes flashed with anger and the chains penetrating her body, glowed white hot, eliciting another scream<BR>                        for Kyt. Another chain leapt out of the darkness and smashed into her, feeling like she had been punched hard in the<BR>                        left shoulder. The other chains vacated her body and she slumped to the floor. When she made to get up, she<BR>                        gasped..but she couldn't scream any more...her arm...her left arm was gone..only a constant spurt of blood.<P>                        The figure began to talk..but not to her..Just to the darkness as if some one else was there.<P><BR>                        "You robbed me of my destiny..My chance to go to Jahorn..." A spiked chain shot out and pierced through Kyt's neck<BR>                        and out of the other side, it retracted slight and she felt barbs at the back of her head as she grasped in disbelief at<BR>                        the chain in front of her, buried in her neck.<P>                        "But I can feel you out there..taunting me...I can feel your power....Every moment. you grow stronger....as do<BR>                        I....soon...we shall meet...and I shall claim my birth right...."<P>                        The chain retreated back into the darkness. Kyt felt no pain... she tumbled forward, finding her self looking at the feet<BR>                        of the figure....the Hell Lord of Palsa, Maxim..as he walked off into the shadows, she heard another thump..and<BR>                        something fell into her view...her twitching headless body. <P>                        Just the last light faded from her, she heard one last word.<P>                        ".....Raziel."<BR>                        -----------------------------------<P>                        A black crescent wave carved the air and into a dozen undead which where immediately disintegrated. But even more<BR>                        took up the fallen's place, all the while still moaning from eternal agony.<P>                        "Dread.....Dread.....Join us.......Dread!!!!!!!!"<P>                        The zombies continued up the hill, pushing through the onslaught undaunted until they came upon an invisible barrier.<BR>                        The zombies howled in pain as the barrier scorched them. On the other side of barrier, a cloaked figure approached the<BR>                        howling zombies, extending an arm. Black hot flames ignited on his arm and a beamed pulsed out destroying the mob of<BR>                        zombies pressed against the barrier.<P>                        The shrouded figure, stepped through to the other side of the barrier into the large gap in the mob of zombies. The<BR>                        zombies closed in encircling the figure, but then suddenly they stopped and didn't close in any further. The figure<BR>                        looked around searching for someone or something. Obviously getting agitated, the figure pulled back the hood of the<BR>                        cloak, revealing a black skinned elf.<P>                        "I tire of this Dread King!!! Show yourself!!"<P>                        The zombies encircling the black elf, began to speak, but instead of the normal moan and chants, they began to speak<BR>                        as one, in a cold almost distant voice.<P>                        "Try as... you might Dirk..... You will never..... be able to hold..... me back forever..."<P>                        "That remains to be seen! You have been trying for 18 years unsuccessfully! You will never enter the temple."<P>                        "...maybe so...but I need not...enter the ruins..to complete my goal......and even Tunare's.....last wish...will not<BR>                        protect..this mountain forever...soon...soon....Dirk Lunas....."<P>                        "Hmph. You are over confident. You will never pierce the barrier. You are too weak. I and others have beaten countless<BR>                        times before and will continue to do so."<P>                        The zombies began to laugh, even Dirk had to shudder at the sound of unnatural sound of thousands of undead<BR>                        laughing as one.<P>                        "My corporeal form may be destroyed....but I will always return...but even so....my new form....will be able to<BR>                        contain...all of my power......not just a token...like Veeshan’s gift......"<P>                        "New form?"<P>                        "In all this time..you do not understand...."<P>                        The zombies began to laugh again.<P>                        "Soon.....the child's soul and corporeal bind...will belong..to me..just ....as the soul and corporeal bind of the..... mother<BR>                        belongs to Palsa......"<P>                        "NEVER!!!" <P>                        The ground surrounding Dirk crackled and then detonated incinerating everything within a quarter mile forward of the<BR>                        barrier. Even with the zombies gone, the voice of the Dread King still spoke.<P>                        "Soon...you will see.....Dirk........Lunas......."<P><BR>                        Then the voice went silent, and the hairs on the back of Dirk's head stopped standing on end, indicating the retreat of<BR>                        the Dread King's influence. He shuddered slightly, then turned around and passed back through the barrier. as he<BR>                        walked back up the mountain in the ButcherBlock range, to Tunare's forgotten temple, his thoughts began to drift.. <P>                        Jesica....I miss you so much..When I have fulfilled my promise...I will avenge you...I will not rest until I have his -<P>                        "Papa! Papa!!!" A small girl appeared out of the temple, and dashed down to greet Dirk. The girl was met with open arms<BR>                        and scooped and lifted into the air.<P>                        "Whee!!!!" she cheered as Dirk twirled around a bit with a large smile Slowing down to a stop, he brought her to his<BR>                        chest and the girl gave him a tight hug around the neck.<P>                        "ack..not so tight Trini." He said feigning ..slightly<P>                        "Sorry."<P>                        "Trini what are you doing up here, you know you aren't supposed to come up here when the zombies approach the<BR>                        temple."<P>                        "I know..but the barrier never lets them through..and even if they did your so strong Papa!!" She said with big eyes<BR>                        swelled with adoration.<P>                        "Yes, I am..but just the same, I don't want you up here when they approach. you're all I have left in the world Trini.<BR>                        now promise me you won't come up here again when the zombies appear."<P>                        " I prom-" Suddenly she shrieked and began to tremble..A cold wave passed over Dirk..he could feel what Trini was<BR>                        feeling. Power...raw unequaled , indescribable power..<P>                        "Papa!! What is it!?!" Trini said between a combination of shakes and tears."<P>                        "I can feel it..A storm.... it's coming."<P>                        ------------------------------<P><BR><center><img>http://gdzks.homestead.com/files/shadow.gif</img></center><BR><center><img>http://gdzks.homestead.com/files/void.gif<img></center><P>------------------------------<P>------------------------------<P><BR>                        (Music Cue| Smackdown: WWF The Music Volume 5)<P>                        Gnomish fireworks sail into the air and explode to the cheers of hundreds of people and blaring music, illuminating the<BR>                        sky.<P>                        {Welcome to Sunday Night Gladiators!!!, 1 mile above the Oasis of Marr in the largest floating arena in Norrath!!!!!! Hi I<BR>                        am Dayn Owens and to my right is, Hermi Pots and we are here to bring you all the details, and moment by moment<BR>                        color commentary on the greatest show in existence!!!}<P>                        (End Music)<P>                        (Music Cue: Bodies: Drowning Pool, Sinners Album)<P>                        {And we are starting things with a bang tonight! First up is a title defense!! and boy is it a doozy!! We are kicking the<BR>                        show off with a defense of the Norrath championship!! Coming down the ramp now is the challenger ..... Commander<BR>                        Slate!!!}<P>                        A large muscular human, enters the massive arena pyrotechnics going off behind him. He raises his arms in celebration,<BR>                        driving the group into greater heights of hysterics<P>                        {I like Co Slate, but personally I think he is way over his head. No one has beaten the champion yet. }<P>                        {I'd have to agree with ya there, but you never know what may happen on SNG}<P>                        (End Music)<P>                        (Music Cue: Smooth Criminal|Alien Ant Farm)<P>                        {And her she comes!! The reigning undefeated champion!! The mean lean fighting machine...AquaMarine!!!}<P>                        {Speaking of machines. Dayn, did you know to wear hard suits, that each suit must be custom fitted tot he wearers<BR>                        body to make an exact fit for the neuro contacts? Obviously making it forming fitting.}<P>                        {I'm a married man..I am happily married man...}<P>                        {And because of the amount of neuro-connection to provide maximum amount of response. The wearer must have<BR>                        nothing underneath the hard suit?}<P>                        {Married Man...Happy, Happy married man!}<P>                        An armored figure steps out, the arena lights up as countless flashes of cameras goes of, shining brightly off the light<BR>                        blue, form fighting hard suit of Aquamarine. The crowd goes insane, as two panels at the shoulder blades of the hard<BR>                        suit open up, jutting out 90 degrees. Aqua marine crouches, an immense flare shoots out of the panels , propelling<BR>                        Aquamarine forward into a breakneck dash down the ramp.. The thruster then suddenly cut out, she falls forward into a<BR>                        several twisting hand springs forward. On the last hand spring, she pushes up, and rights her self, the thrusters kick in<BR>                        again, and she connects to Slate with a tremendous Arial whirlwind kind.<P>                        (End Music Cue)<BR>                        --------------------------<P>                        Wow, Aquamarine is tough.<P>                        |She's ok.|<P>                        Like to see you do that.<P>                        |Fat chance.|<P>                        Thought so old man<P>                        |I may be old but I can still kick your butt!!!|<P>                        I am so scared..I quake at the thought of you batting me with your paw.|<P>                        |You know in my day, people actually respected their grandpa.|<P>                        Tough noogies<P>                        With the last remark, Reyas batted the young boy in the head with his paw.<P>                        "ow!"<P>                        |You deserve it. Now do you want to pay off the airship or not?"<P>                        Of course...though I don't see why I have to do the hard part? it's your fault that it broke in the first place.<P>                        |It is not!!! I was just walking there!! Even if it was my fault...which it is not. You don't expect your poor old Granpa to<BR>                        do hard labor now do you?|<P>                        Oh so now you are old and wornout?<P>                        |O yes..O my back...O ah..ee oi! How does that sound?|<P>                        Hmph!<P>                        |Being more then several millennia old has it's benefits|<P>                        So I am learning...Alright..I'l go get ready. You go place the bet. And no stopping at the Casino this time!!<P>                        |You have no faith in me Nall...sniff.....|<P>                        You better believe it! Now promise!!<P>                        |Alright I promise I won’t stop at the Casino.|<P>                        And...<P>                        |..the bar..|<P>                        And!!!<P>                        |...the Hall of Scantily Clad Elves....Man! you are no fun.| With a sigh, the silver winged cat Reyas, hopped off the<BR>                        Nall's shoulder and disappeared around the corner.<BR>                        ---------------------------<P>                        A door chirps.<P>                        "Enter."<P>                        A gnome holding a data assistant pad, enters the dark room and stands in front of a large oak desk, staring at the back<BR>                        of the chair of the Director of En-gen. A small puff of smoke drifts up from behind the chair. A flash of lightning goes<BR>                        off, illuminating the dark room.<P>                        "Could this be any more of a cliche? You have to much free time boss."<P>                        The man in the chair laughed, then thumbed a button on his chair. The room illuminated, the tv in front of him<BR>                        disappears into the ceiling, the smoke generator on the top of chair, retracted into the chair, and the chair it self<BR>                        shurnk down to 3/4 it's previous size as does the table. The chair swings aroun