 energy, the wave was so forceful it lifted the super<BR>                        heavy man and sent him flying across the arena, landing not to far from his partner. <P>                        {HOLY!!! WOW!! Have you ever seen anything like that? Lets count the hits in super slo-mo!!! 1...2...10.......Incredible,<BR>                        not counting that massive energy wave a breathtaking 56 hits all in 4 seconds!!! Unbelievable!!!!!!} <P>                        Nall collapse on knee, panting heavily from the expenditure. But the cheers pf the crowd, got the adrenaline flowing and<BR>                        he got back up to his feet and waked tot he center of the ring and raised his arms in triumph!<P>                        YEAH!!! I RULE!!!!! AND THE 'NEKKID ELF' WILL FLY AGAIN!!!!<P>                        "ALRIG-" <P>                        "I'M NOT THROIUGH WITH YOU YET!!!!"<P>                        "What the-" Nall whirled around to see the massive Tank back on his feet charging toward him<P>                        {NO WAY!!!}<BR>                        |NO WAY!!!|<BR>                        "NO WAY!!!"<P>                        But before Tank could get close a massive beam seemed to come out from no were and burn a large 5 foot hole<BR>                        between him and Nall.<P>                        "Who?"<P>                        {Who shot that particle beam?...Look up on the arena spire!!!! It's... It's!!}<P>                        |Aquapurine!!!|<P>                        -Marine.<P>                        |What ever.|<P>                        Standing tall arms folded, balanced on the high reaching spire of the floating arena was the SNG champion, Aquamarine.<BR>                        Her shoulder canon still smoking retracted back inside of the hardsuit.<P>                        "You!! It's bad enough that a puny little girl is the champion!@!! now you want to interfere in my match!!! I have had<BR>                        enough you girlie!!!" shouted Tank "FIRE ALL MISSLES!!"<P>                        Tank disappeared in a cloud of smoke as 13 missiles leapt out of various places of his armor suit and streaked toward<BR>                        Aquamarine.<P>                        {What is he doing? Why waste missiles, he can't Aquamarine she's above the Crowd Protection sh- OH MY GOD!!!! The<BR>                        missiles just went through the shield!!!! If they hit the spire who knows how many will be hurt or killed!!!!}<P>                        The panicked crowds screamed loudly, but it was not because of the thought of the missiles hitting tall spire , it was<BR>                        out of reaction of an ear piercing noise emanating from Aquamarine.<P>                        GAAAAAAAAAAAAAHHH!!!!<P>                        |WHAT IN THE HELL IS THAT!!!!|<P>                        The missiles!!! Look the sound is causing them to detonate high and out of the way. Aquamarine saved the crowd!!!<P>                        As the ear piercing screeched died out, Aquamarine somersaulted through the air and landed in front of Tank. Planting a<BR>                        fist into his faceplate and then an armored leg into his groin dropping the behemoth.<P>                        Nall still somewhat dazed from the sound, watched through the haze as aquamarine then moonsaulted and dropped<BR>                        down the large hole she caused with her shoulder canon.<P>                        {Hey where is Aquamarine going? Wait a sec....Isn't that area of the floor above the ..OH NO!!!!!}<P>                        Aquamarine reappeared out of the hole carrying three very large jingling sacks. Turning toward the dazed Nall, she lifted<BR>                        her Visor showing her face to him. <P>                        "Thanks for driving up the loot cutie. I owe ya!" She blew him a kiss and snapped down the visor. Crouching down for a<BR>                        moment, she leapt 50 feet into the air and then her thrusters kicked in sending her flying upward and away.<P>                        |NALL!!! You got to stop her!! She just robbed the place!!!! All our winnings is in those bags!!!|<P>                        No need to tell me twice!<P>                        Nall crouched down and leapt up into the air, but instead of thrusters, he spread his expansive wings and took after<BR>                        her.<P>                        "Come back here you...you!! Blue Platinum stealer you!!!!"<P>                        Flying under her, he swiped at her breastplate which she easily dodged. He swiped at her several times, missing again<BR>                        and again. seeing that she had no way of escaping without fighting him, she let go of the bags, and with a sudden<BR>                        quickness grasped Nall and head butted him. As stars circled around him, she cut her thrusters and began to fall back<BR>                        down toward the arena him tight in her grasp.<P>                        {Oh no!! Looks she has him set up for her signature move!! The Waterfall!!!}<P>                        Her thrusters kicked in as the plummeted head first, the arena grew larger and larger, and then she kicked of him letting<BR>                        him continue on his own.<P>                        {OH!!!! 1.....2.....3...AH...4..Geez!!...5...6!!! Man she just drove him down through 6 floors of the Arena. And that's<BR>                        reinforced Velium!! Some one get a cleric for this kid!}<P>                        Aquamarine continued back up into the sky, diverting just enough to catch the falling bags filled to the brim with<BR>                        platinum coins. A second pair of thrusters angled out and she rocketed up into the night sky.<P>                        ...women............................ow.....<P>                        6 floors down under the arena, Nall's world went black.<P>                        |NALL!!!!! Answer me!!!!!!! NALL!|<P>                        The winged silver cat Reyas sifted through the mess of velium and mythril searching desperately for his grandson. After<BR>                        a few minutes, he came upon a patch of white fur. <P>                        |Nall!!!!!|<P>                        Reaching in he pulled out a small white winged kitten with a red diamond on its forehead. Shaking the kitten for a few<BR>                        moment, it mewed grumpily.<P>                        Think it's to late to try the Antonican lottery? ow......<P>                        The kitten Nall, dozed off to sleep again.<BR>                        -------------------------------------<P>                        Not too far away. On the top of one of mountain peaks in the Oasis of Marr. A figure wearing a two horned mask of<BR>                        crystal, watched what happened above. As the events unfolded and concluded. The figure began to talk to itself. at<BR>                        first it was a man's voice.<P>                        "Things are starting once again. The void is growing restless and stretching out more and more. The teachings have<BR>                        gotten it excited, it must not be allowed o be free...I should have listened to you."<P>                        The voice continued talking to itself but this time it was a woman's voice.<P>                        *You hold to much guilt. Why do you always take so much upon your shoulders?"*<P>                        Then back to the man's<P>                        "Because it is my fate not to rest until things are right. I owe her that much."<P>                        *But why do you place such a have penance upon yourself. You could have brought her back long ago. It was well<BR>                        within your grasp.*<P>                        "With the knowledge of what I have done to this world..and the pain I put on her I could not bear to look upon her. I<BR>                        would only see pain..nothing but endless pain."<P>                        *You are so melodramatic...but that is one thing I have always loved about you. It was why I picked you, because you<BR>                        don't find the easy way out..but even so. You don't have to take it this far. You can have some happiness.*<P>                        "Maybe...but not today. Only when the Void has been silenced."<P>                        *Yes.*<P>                        The two voices began to speak together, almost as one, but overlapping each other.<P>                        "The influence of the Void must wiped from Norrath and from al things. It must not be freed. It is our task, our duty to<BR>                        ensure that the Universe knows not the touch of the void. And it shall forever be our task, we are one in this, we<BR>                        are........ Rashan."<BR>                        ---------------------------<BR>                        End of Chapter 1<BR>                        ---------------------------<P><BR>--------------------------------<BR>                        En-Gen Biological Data file. Code Blue Eyes Only<BR>                        --------------------------------<P><BR>                        Subject: Maxim Tidias<BR>                        Profession: Hell Lord of High City Palsa<BR>                        Age: Estimated to be over 500 years old<BR>                        MTA Level: Unchartable<BR>                        Race: Erudite<BR>                        Last Known Location: High City Palsa<BR>                        En-Gen Filer: Shamus Actus<P>                        Bio: <P>                        Maxim Tidias is the current Hell Lord for the High City Palsa. He acquired this rank, through less then perfect<BR>                        circumstances, which has lead to recent events and discovery of other potent subjects for integration into the Ghost<BR>                        Program and Lilith.<P><BR>                        From what that can be extracted from old scrolls. Maxim was one of Raziel Eom’brn’s students at the Rank of Hell<BR>                        Knight. For all that can be told, it was said that Maxim was immensely powerful even then, but unlike his current state,<BR>                        he was easy going and for the most part cheerful and happy. But that was changed about 500 years ago, when the<BR>                        people of the now destroyed city of Erudin, attacked the also destroyed city of Paineel.<P>                        In the attack, his love was mortally wounded and later died in his arms as the old cliché goes. Bringing out the cold,<BR>                        torturous Maxim that we know of now. The death of his love, also a Hell Knight Reva, sealed his heart in ice, and the<BR>                        only pleasure he ever received from then on was the slow torturing of those who opposed him, with his shadow chains.<P>                        Because of Raziel’s flight from Paineel, Maxim being the only surviving Hell Knight (being this after torturing and slaying<BR>                        the other student of Raziel.), Maxim was promoted to the rank of Hell Lord.<P>                        Unfortunately for him, custom and lore states that He is not a true Hell Lord and may never enter the sacred ‘Halls of<BR>                        Jahorn’ (A mythical place, to the Hell Lords, where there souls go after death.), because he never defeated his mentor<BR>                        Raziel. This just further agitated Maxim, driving him even more insane then his mentor. (As unbelievable as that<BR>                        sounds).<P>                        Flash forward 500 years to the present. Maxim is still the Hell Lord, and at this point he has tortured and consumed the<BR>                        souls of hundreds and hundreds of his students and countless others. His heart of ice over the years has grown colder<BR>                        and his mind even more unstable until one day he meets a woman capable of piercing the ice, and for a time he almost<BR>                        seemed stable.<P>                        But things like this are never perfect, as it turns out the woman that eased his suffering, was the wife of one of our<BR>                        targets Dirk Lunas (See file Dirk). <P>                        For reason unknown, she left him after the brief 2-month affair, returning to Dirk. This of course drove Maxim, insane<BR>                        beyond all point of recovery.<P>                        Interestingly enough, the woman later returned some time later and was promptly killed by Maxim. Though her death<BR>                        wasn’t his usual MO. It was quick and without (for the most part) pain.<P><BR>                        Summary: Maxim is a valuable subject for the projects. A sample of him is required immediately. Though there are few<BR>                        subjects that I would like to delve into deeper, when I can spare the time. One, through out his reign as Hell Lord or<BR>                        even back when he was just a Knight. No one ever saw his familiar. It can only be speculated that, he chooses to hide<BR>                        it for when he needs the familiar's power..which makes you wonder just how powerful can Maxim be?<P>                        End of File<BR>                        En-Gen Bio-Research Head Shamus Actus<BR>                        ----------------------------------------<P>                        Subject: Dirk Lunas<BR>                        Profession: Unknown<BR>                        Age: Estimated to be over 500 years old<BR>                        MTA Level: Unchartable<BR>                        Race: Combinate Creature (High Elf and Unknown)<BR>                        Last Known Location: ButcherBlock protected zone, Continent Faydwer <BR>                        En-Gen Filer: Shamus Actus<P>                        Bio: <P>                        Dirk Lunas, probably one of the most reclusive and hard to find subjects ever tracked. There is not much to report<BR>                        specifically about him; from old records it is known that he is a master of Shadow Magic, supposedly a ‘God’ level magic<BR>                        form.<P>                        On the other hand there is a great wealth of information about the people around him. More specifically his wife. He<BR>                        lived with her for a great period of time inside the Butcherblock protected area. For the most part that is were they<BR>                        stayed, only occasionally visiting the outside world.<P>                        In one of these outings his wife met and had an affair with Maxim Tidias (See file Maxim). The affair was brief however,<BR>                        and she retuned to Dirk. But this brings up an interesting possibility. About 2 years after the affair and her return she<BR>                        gave birth to a child, because of the wildly varying gestation periods (5 months-3 years) of elves and half-breed elves.<BR>                        It is unknown if the child was fathered by Maxim or Dirk. But regardless of the child’s father, she must contain<BR>                        extraordinaire power. Which is why En-Gen is very interested in her, not to mention the Dread king who dominates the<BR>                        accused continent.<P>                        Summary: Dirk Lunas and his(if she is his) child are valuable subjects and a sample must be obtained. Also considering<BR>                        the constant attacks by the Dread King and his knowledge of Shadow Magic, I recommend that we take a sample of<BR>                        Dirk and liquidate him, but extract the child from Faydwer and bring her back to En-Gen. Not only can we obtain<BR>                        samples from her, but also considering her young age and impressionability, she could be recruited to one of our<BR>                        programs.<P>                        End of File
