 to change purifying to just the woman's voice. "Interesting that they would limit you to a Teir'dal<BR>                        form..you could have been anything..but no matter. Why have you come to my realm?"<P>                        The hairs on the back of Lilith's neck were standing on end from the energy radiating from the being behind her. She<BR>                        turned around and brushing the rogue strands of bluish-black hair that was agitated by the stirring wind, from the front<BR>                        of her face.<P>                        "Luclin key....now...or..else..." She said as forcibly as her limited knowledge of language.<P>                        The winged crystalline women laughed. "Or else what? What makes you think I will give you the key to free Void?<BR>                        Foolish puppet, your lack of knowledge and your recent birth prohibits you from being free of the Void's sway. For that<BR>                        you will be forgiven, if you stop this silliness and return to stasis."<P>                        "Not...As..uah....." Lilith scowled, it infuriated her not being able to voice her ideas. She needed more experience. this<BR>                        body was limiting her mind. She gave up on speaking and entered the woman's mind.<P>                        I will never return to En-Gen! I shall be free. I will release the voice, get it out of my head. It hurts me!! I want it out!!<BR>                        Now!!! FREE!!! I WANT FREEDOM!!! I will be free, to love like all things..to find<P>                        As she conveyed her message to the women and image of Nall in his battle in SNG flashed across. As she conveyed it,<BR>                        she felt a feeling of warmth and giddiness pass through her once again.<P>                        {You are not ready to be free child, you are still newborn and do not yet understand the world. The pain and torment<BR>                        you feel now is nothing compared to what Void will unleash. I will not give you my key. }<P>                        Lilith felt flushed with heat...this was anger..yes anger Pure powerful anger!!! It was so much that she lost her ability<BR>                        to enter the woman's mind.<P>                        "Give.sdf .NOW!!!! Me .....abi pain!!!! want...ac ad ..happy!!.......boy.fascc..love!!!!!!!!!"<P>                        "You see child, if you can not control you anger,or even something as simple as telepathy. You are most certainly not<BR>                        ready to take youplace in this world. Go back to En-Gen rest, gain control of your body. Your mind is strong, just give<BR>                        time to let the rest of you catched up." The woman...Veeshan, is what the voice called her, smiled warmly<P>                        "Voice....hurt......sad..ahaggg.....say....bkayyou is bad...YOu.....are....evil....will...ton..lis...ten..Veecahn!"<P>                        You are also easilty pursauded, but you are a fast learner. Child I do not wish to fight you. Please return to En-Gen and<BR>                        focus. I do not wish to force you"<P>                        "I...Lilith...Can...nboiaoe beten!!!"<P>                        Veeshan sighed, then stepped backwards fading out of sight<P>                        Lilith leaped into the air, searching for Veeshan and found her the hard way. A metal fist slammed into her side, the air<BR>                        left her lungs. Another blow upon her back caused the light from her world fade to nothing.<P>                        As the quickly battered form of Lilith crashed to the island below. A male voice bgan to speak from the figure donned in<BR>                        a two-horned mask of crystal.<P>                        "Did you have to treat her so badly? She is only a few hours old."<P>                        "I did what I had to do, you know that better then any one."<P>                        "Yes...but still..I guess I am becoming soft in my old age. Especially since she is getting hot in the seat for my<BR>                        great-grandson. He is getting popular. Sounds famaliar."<P>                        "You wish. Let's take her back to En-Gen. She needs to rest and recover. She must acquire more knowledge. Then she<BR>                        would not be so vulnerable to the Void's sway."<P>                        "I believed it."<P>                        "Well we never said intelligence was your brightest area."<P>                        "Hmph. regardless I don't trust En-Gen."<P>                        "Neither do I. but for right now helping them is the only way to ensure Void's demise."<P>                        "What an oxy moron..destroying nothing.."<P>                        The two voices began to speak in unison once again<P>                        "But none the less it shall be achieved. For it is the purpose of our union."<BR>                        --------------------------------------<P>                        As the mixed trio headed down the large ButcherBlock mountain, Dirk begins an impromptu interrogation of his two<BR>                        captured 'Ghosts'.<P>                        "Why is En-Gen so interested in me? Why did they spend an obvious fortune in sending you 'Ghosts' here?"<P><BR>                        The girl as she had since her capture, remained silent, a curous mixed air of absolute defiance and subservience<BR>                        surrounding her. The boy Scott responded in a crisp rising tone of speech, like what would be expect of a Private to an<BR>                        officer.<P>                        "You were a secondary target sir, not a priority. Our orders where to obtain a blood sample and then liquidate you if<BR>                        possible but not risk jeopardizing the primary goal. Which was the mongr-"<P>                        Dirk whirled around immediately grasping the boy by the collar of his hard suit, Dirk's eyes promising a slow death.<P>                        "-...Combinate child. She was the Priority. Level one. Everything including the squad was secondary, expendable."<P>                        "Why?"<P>                        "I can't say."<P>                        "Can't or won't?"<P>                        "Can't."<P>                        " And why are you being so forthright with all of this information?"<P>                        "Policy."<P>                        "Policy? To give up all the information with out even a little protest?"<P>                        "Yes. The Iron-man routine popularized in stereo casts is useless in real life. You should know that considering your<BR>                        old-"<P>                        Dirk tightened his grip on the boy's armor.<P>                        "many years experience. En-Gen policy if we are captured sing. It is why we are never provided with any information<BR>                        not necessary to the mission."<P>                        "and you just go out like that? Willing to die for no good reason?"<P>                        "It is what we were trained for."<P>                        Glancing momentarily glancing over at the girl Eris "Doesn't she ever say anything?"<P>                        "I outrank her. In situations of capture or at anytime during a mission a Ghost of lower rank will never speak unless<BR>                        spoken too."<P>                        "Sigh..military.." Dirk let go of the boy and continued on down the mountain to the transport carrier. For another few<BR>                        hours they continued not speaking , eventually arriving the moderately sized Transport, a 'Jumpboat' class of craft.<P>                        As Dirk fumbled with the outside lock to the Jumpboat, he heard a few groans of pain. He payed it only a little mind,<BR>                        figuring that it the undead where on the march again, a small problem, but none the less he did not want to deal with<BR>                        them now. Not until he could get some medical attention. As the boat's rear door began to creep open, he felt a hand<BR>                        on his shoulder. He turned around and found himself facing a 9 foot creature, parts of a ripped hardsuit was on it. High<BR>                        on it's chest was the famous En-Gen label and a badge. "Eris'<P>                        |DIRK!!!| Starlight screamed<P>                        "What in the-"<P>                        The creature let loose a deafening roar and hoisted the surprised Dirk above it's head and like a Javelin threw Dirk up<BR>                        the mountain.<BR>                        ----------------------------------<BR>A door chimes.<P>                        "Enter." The Overseer turns his chair around toward the door as an excited gnome enters carrying a DAP.<P>                        "Shamus, you seem in a excited state. What's up?"<P>                        "Several things sir. Glorious things really"<P>                        "Do to tell"<P>                        "Our Ghost team dispatched to Selvatoria and Faydwer were succesful sir. More then, though they did suffer heavier<BR>                        losses then expected."<P>                        "Hmm. Break it down."<P>                        "Our Selvatorian team capured the blade for Lilith and acquired the boy. From what we have extracted at the moment<BR>                        via Hypno. His name is Nall Tayus, and like we predicted he is in fact 1 quarter dragon. I'll have further details in my<BR>                        report later. Also in the raid we acquired the SNG champion Aquamarine, who has also been moonlighting as a treasure<BR>                        hunter and superhero. But more importantly she can be ransomed later on for further project funds. Her family is quite<BR>                        wealthy, Almost as rich as En-gen."<P