<BR>                        Lunas and it is currently being integrated into Lilith as we speak. 2. We acquired the child and are running a complete<BR>                        work up on her in our Deep six station underneath Timorous. But what we have gotten with just prelim's is<BR>                        unbelievable."<P>                        "What?"<P>                        "We determined her father."<P>                        "Who?"<P>                        "Dirk AND Maxim"<P>                        "WHAT !?! That's impossible!"<P>                        "Yes as unbelievable as it sounds. Both Maxim and Dirk are the chld's father. We have no idea how this happened, but<BR>                        she has a profile matching the mother, Dirk and Maxim. This is just incredible. Even at her young age, she is already<BR>                        exhibiting fantastic powers, at this moment her potential MT level already matches Lilith. This more then explains the<BR>                        Dread King's interest in her, by the gods, if he hadn't extracted her and that barrier failed. I hate to think about it." <P>                        "A small child like that, born of woman matching the collective work of years and of research..unbelievable. I trust you<BR>                        are integrating her profile in Lilith?"<P>                        "Of course!"<P>                        "Speaking of the child what of the father..er one of the fathers. Dirk?"<P>                        "Unfortunately he is still alive though heavily injured. At the moment we suspect, he is interrogating the remaining<BR>                        Ghosts. Should we explode their hearts sir?"<P>                        "What? No don't be silly. They may be 1st generation, but they are still valuable..for now. Lets keep our 40 million<BR>                        platinum investments. "<P>                        The Overseer opens a panel on his table and depresses a button.<P>                        |Stratospheric monitoring online Overseer|<P>                        "Switch to Final Heavan.."He smiles at Shamus" Camera 3b and display"<P>                        A holographic image of an Arial view of Faydwer, floats in the air at head level of the Overseer. <P>                        "Target Ghost Units in area and Lock on"<P>                        |Acquiring......Target Lock...Fire Final Heavan?|<P>                        "No."<P>                        |Final Heavan powering down from Stratospheric strike readiness. What is your order Overseer?|<P>                        "Activate Neoteny. Code Overseer Alpha One"<P>                        |Code accepted.. Neoteny Genetic Transmutation Activated. Do you wish to magnify and enhance view Overseer?|<P>                        "No. You've seen one bloodbath, you've seen another. Display off."<P>                        "Hmph. Bloodbath is a polite way of putting it. Sir, why did you want Lilith to be transported on the Qeynos flagship? It<BR>                        is rather slow."<P>                        "I know, but our recent actions have been picking up a lot of negative media and public attention. Especially when we<BR>                        use our own resources, who ever thought of the the public's right to know, needs to be dragged out into the steet and<BR>                        shot."<P>                        "Which street?"<P>                        "oo..I dunno.. how about all of them?"<P>                        As the two continued to discuss other matters, far away on the undead continent of Faydwer. The two Ghost's, Eris<BR>                        and Scott, began to cry out in pain, as their bodies began to rip and tear. Muscles and sinew shredded, rgrew and<BR>                        swelled. No longer where they pinnacles of stealth and covert operations. They where monsters demons<BR>                        almost..designed for one thing and one thing only. To destroy everything in their path.<BR>                        ---------------------------------------<P>Blackness then stars... everything was spinning around..<P>                        "Where are am I?" Dirk mumbled<P>                        |I suggest you get up and fast you have two big uglies coming toward you| Starlight suggested<P>                        "Who are ...you? Star..li?" Two heavy thuds sounded behind him. Dirk groggily rotated around to face to large demonic<BR>                        creatures. Standing 9 feet tall and rippling muscle adorned in mangled metal/ceramic armor. They stared directly into his<BR>                        eyes and roared so lud that the ground quaked.<P>                        "Oh shi-"<P>                        One of them piced him up like a doll and began to slam him up and down against the jagged rock, inflicting more wounds<BR>                        on the battered Black Elf. After a baker's dozen of slams the creature hoisted him up so they where face to face. It<BR>                        opened it's great maw and roared once again as millions of volts of electricity coursed through. As much as it hurt Dirk<BR>                        did not cry out, unknown if it was for bracery or for inabilty from the amount current flowing through. Soon the beast<BR>                        let up, Dirk hung limp. It roared was again and let his body drop to the dirt. The beast growled once and then with the<BR>                        other prepared to head down the mountain. It crouched down to make a leap but just as it tensed a fist smashed into<BR>                        it's spine shattering it. Before the beast could howl two hands wrapped around it's mouth and face and yanked down<BR>                        and backwards right into a hard knee, knocking the beast out.<P>                        The other was somewhat surprised from the swiftness and power of Dirk's return assualt, the moments hesitation was<BR>                        more then enough for Dirk. In then that brief moment, mana gathered within Dirk's body.<P>                        "Nocturne Beam!" The beam of darkness struck the best in the chest, melting the chest plate and catapulting the beast<BR>                        of the cliff.<P>                        "Man...I need a vacation.."<P>                        |Well no rest for you yet Dirk. We still have to find Trini.|<P>                        The reminder of Trini,, momentarily eased his wounds and salved his numerous burns.<P>                        "Yes.But where to start?"<P>                        |I'm sure that the transport has a course already in the auto pilot. It may be a good place to start.|<P>                        "Yes.."<P>                        Picking him self of the cold rock, he slowly limped down the mountain to the Jumpboat. His resolve unwavering but his<BR>                        wounds soon began to take it's toll and even Dirk's might couldn't keep up forever. Luckily the craft was in reach, he<BR>                        stumbled inside and as he began to black out, he thumbed the autopilot.<P>                        |Rest well, Dirk|<BR>                        --------------------------------<P>                        Nall slowly opened his eyes, he could still taste the chloroform. <P>                        "Yech.."<P>                        "Yeah. I know you would have thought the could have given me a decent shirt to wear."<P>                        That voice seemed familiar...it wasn't..it couldn't be.. he opened his eyes and looked up...it was<P>                        "Aquamarine!?!"<P>                        He stared at the human girl in the ragged dirty oily shirt and mechanics pants.<P>                        "Yes. Looks like we are stuck together."<P>                        "Great. I lose all my money, find a way to make some, you interfere, again! And no I have been capture by the gods<BR>                        only know and I am once again with you!"<P>                        "Seems like you have a crush."<P>                        "Wha.AJ I..You.." Nal stammered in a flustered state<P>                        Aquamarine giggled as Nall's face began to match the red strip of hair above his brow.<P>                        "Hehe. Look for what it's worth, I'm sorry about what happened on SNG."<P>                        "And what about now?"<P>                        "Oh, this your fault"<P>                        "My fault! None of this would have happened if you hadn't butted in!"<P>                        " Doesn't matter now" "...even though it is your fault" she mumbles<P>                        "Huh?"<P>                        "Nothing. So what is your name? YOur real name I mean unless you like being called Kid Draco?"<P>                        "No most definitely not. Nall."<P>                        "Annie..my real name is Anita but I prefer Annie. I wonder what they want from us on a Battle cruiser?"<P>                        "Battle cruiser?"<P>                        "Yeah, we are on the Qeynoes Royal Battle cruiser Gunboat Diplomat. The largest and most powerful sea-based craft<BR>                        on Norrath."<P>                        "I thought the Palsian 'cruiser Limiting Factor was the most powerful ship?"<P>                        Annie fumed and turn red, angry red not the embarrassed red Nall was. "IT IS NOT!! MY DA-..I mean the Diplomat is<BR>                        biggest most powerful ship on Norrath."<P>                        "Whatever. It's just another sailboat"<P>                        Annie grew even redder, Nall oblivious to her rising anger sighed loudly lamenting about his still broken Airship.<P>                        "I don't think you know of any way to get out of here do you?"<P>                        "No..well. there is one way but we don't have blow torch."<P>                        "What? melt the hinges of the door?"<P>                        "No, thats reinforced Quatain, straight from the deepest Selvatorian mines. JUst like my suit....That stuff is hard is<BR>                        damage."<P>                        "Then what?"<P><BR>                        "See the air shaft above me? "<P>                        "Yeah?"<P>                        "That's just ordinary steel, if we had something hot enough, one of us could scamper across and out of the airshaft in<BR>                        the main hallway and open the cell."<P>                        "Hmm..How do you know all this?"<P>                        "I..um..read alot of books and stuff on battleships...anyway there's no point, we don't have blow-torch."<P>                        "Well, maybe not a blowtorch..but I have something that can melt the steel."<P>                        "What?"<P>                        "Me."<P>                        "You?"<P>                        "Yes, me"<P>                        "How?"<P>                        "you'll see" Nal closed his eyes and his body began to shimmer. In a flash, Nall disappeared, except for a pill of clothes<BR>                        laying against the cell wall.<P>                        "What the?"<P>                        Annie crawled over to the clothes, wondering where Nall went. Then she noticed a small bump wriggling around inside of<BR>                        Nall's shirt and a small squeaky voice called out.<P>                        "Heeeelp..."<P>                        Bewildered she opened the shirt revealing a small winged white kitten with a red diamond patch of fur on it's forehead.<BR>                        It mewed and then began to speak.<P>                        "Thanks"<P>                        "Nall?"<P>                        "Yes, it's me" he purred<P>                        "Oh your so cute!!" She held hm tightly and squeezed<P>                        "GAAAAH!! Kitten in pain!! Let go of kitty!!!"<P>                        Annie either ignored or didn't her him as she kept squeezing him, for a few more moments then she yelled trying to put<BR>                        out her shirt, which was on fire.<P>                        After patting out the small fire, she glowered at the kitten huddled on the pile of clothes.<P>                        "YOu little!" She lunged to grab him, but he spoke stopping her "WAIT! Straggle me later, first lift me up to the airshaft<BR>                        so I can melt it."<P>                        "I thought you could fly?"<P>                        "Not in this form. Sigh, I'm too young and I don't have enough dragon inside me to fly in minor form. Sigh I can only fly<BR>                        as you originally new me."<P>                        "Dragon? You're really a dragon? And I thought that was just a stupid name."<P>                        "Quarter -Dragon. And no before you ask I can not enlarge to the big stereotypical dragon! Only granpa can do that.<BR>                        Hey, where is he?"<P>                        "We have been the only ones here. Maybe he is in another cell?"<P>                        "Maybe"<P>                        Granpa ,you ok?<P>                        After a few moments. Nall frowned. <P>                        "he''s not here or if he is, he is unconscious. I can't here his thoughts..which should normally be easy, they are pretty<BR>                        loud and consistent. well either way, lets get out of here. Lift me up"<P>                        Using his fiery breath, Nall made short work of the steel bars and scampered up into the airshaft. A few moments later,<BR>                        outside in the hallway a guard cried out and then thudded t the ground unconscious. Then, the tumblers on the cell<BR>                        door clicked loudly and the door slid open and Nall stepped inside.<P>                        "TADA! Happy to see me?"<P>                        "Not really, but I take it you're happy to see me?" she said with an devilish smile<P>                        Nall turned red again "HEY! HEY! Turn around!"<P>                        She giggled and complied as Nall got his clothes back on.<P>                        "Stop peeking!"<BR>                        -------------------------------------<BR>Eris moaned loudly and then cried out as she ripped of what remained of her chest plate, taking some flesh with it. She<BR>                        curled up and cried, not from her wounds and broken bones, but from agony. She had felt her body grow and swell as<BR>                        the chemicals contained in her hard-suit flooded though, she could feel every cell gorge on the raw power and ignite.<BR>                        She could feel all her control dissolve; it was like being a puppet on strings. She had no control on what she had tried<BR>                        to inflict on that man...who seemed nice when he wasn't being assaulted, she was aware of everything, but unable to<BR>                        stop. Though she never admitted it..except to Scott, she hated fighting and killing. She always held back, which is why<BR>                        she put in the 'backward' Ghost unit. In a way she was glad, it was her timidness that saved her, and her affection, as<BR>                        forbidden as it was, for Scott which saved him. <P>                        Being unable to hold back, inflicting pain and suffering, hurt her more then anything she could have ever inflict. But that<BR>                        wasn't the beginning of her pain, she could here some else's moans.<P>                        Scott!<P>                        Getting up as fast as she could, she clicked the mangled jump jet in her suit, risking detonation and shot up the cliff to<BR>                        find Scott, laying on jagged rock.<P>                        "SCOTT!" She fell down beside him and cradles him.<BR>----------
