gn of life at all. Relieved and disappointed at the same time, Reyas limped up the ramp<BR>                        and entered the craft, his eyes constantly scanning looking for something, which he was rewarded for.<P>                        "DIE YOU SCUM!!!"<P>                        A prism blade flashed out of nowhere, colliding with Reyas's sword emitting a shower of sparks. Holding the blade away<BR>                        with one hand, he aimed his other in the darkness where the blade was coming from and cast a spell.<P>                        "Grav Disruption" A ripple emitted from his hand and the unseen assailant grunted and flew backwards into the wall of<BR>                        the ship.<P>                        "ow..sonofa..." The form got back to it's feet and charged again<P>                        "You En-gen punks don't learn do you." Reyas extended both of us hands "Grav Disruption" The form smashed into the<BR>                        wall again. This time Reyas's charged sword at ready and just as suddenly stopped, the attacker finally coming into<BR>                        view. A Black elf in a mangled hardsuit, but not a En-gen suit.<P>                        "You're not with En-gen!!" They both said in surprised noticing the lack of the glaring En-Gen label.<P>                        "No kidding. Who are you?" They said at the same time again.<P>                        "My name is Reyas."<P>                        "Dirk..Dirk Lunas...help me up will you..man you pack a punch. either that or I am getting old...maybe both.ow my<BR>                        back."<P>                        "You don't even know the meaning of old." Reyas smirked, pulling the battered Dirk up to his feet. <P>                        "Man, your in bad shape" They said at the same time again studying each other.<P>                        "That is getting old, and yeah. Not surprising after getting jumped by some of En-gen's goons, not to mention being<BR>         