. Only the strong should protect Norrath and that is not you."<P>                        "And you are? Haha! You are already succumbing to the Void's influence as we speak. It is only a matter of time till you<BR>                        serve the Void. Not even your femine half can protect you."<P>                        "I need no one to protect me nor do I serve any one." Raziel levitated off the pillar and began to radiate with power<BR>                        "But I tire of this petty banter ..Za'Amor"<P>                        If it where possible, it almost seemed like the Faceless one flinched at the sound of his true name. Raziel outstretched<BR>                        his hand to the god and his terrible weapon the black flame demon blade, the Kirosawa materialized<P>                        "Give ...me... your Key!"<P>                        The Faceless roared with laughter. "Fool. You have had the key for half a millennia."<P>                        "What!?!" <P>                        "Still do not realize, the key is a mimc, just like your other halfs key. Can't you feel it twisting your soul. Destroying you<BR>                        from the inside? Can't you feel the nothingness stretch across your being? Memories you once cherished now gone?"<P>                        Raziel for the first time found himself dumbstruck for a few moments, slowly recovering he extended his other hand and<BR>                        a katana of purest crystal materialized, the Nagitaka, Veeshan's blade. <P>                        You didn't tell me!?!<P>                        Raziel..I ...<P>                        YOU....<P>                        Raz..<P>                        SHUT UP!!!<P>                        Raziel ignited with flames as his anger took hold of him. The Nagitaka vanished and Raziel leapt at the faceless one,<BR>                        burying the Kirosawa deep into the god. Instead of cries of pain the god laughed.<P>                        "Before I destroy you. Tell me, why where the keys created in the first place! Why give Void a chance to return!"<P>                        The go laughed again "That you will have to ask to your other side...my reaver. Go forth and dance upon the strings of<BR>                        Void..."<P>                        The god disappeared, leaving Raziel alone. As Raziel disappeared into the shadows to return to Norrath, Cazic-Thule's<BR>                        laughter continued amongest the renewed screams of the damned.<BR>                        -------------------------------------<BR>The pistol rest against his forehead. The hammer ****ed and ready. A dove flew in and sat on the window. It walked<BR>                        around the sill for a few moments and then leapt away frightened at the loud noise of gunshot. The pistol clattered on<BR>                        the ground, Reyas full of weariness turned to his hand where the pistol once was, to stare at the distraught and<BR>                        terrified face of Dyane<BR>                        .<P>                        "WHAT ARE YOU DOING!?!"<P>                        "Leave me alone. Let me die in peace."<P>                        "Papa." Dyane begin to cry and clutched her father. Reyas shook her off.<P>                        "Go away...I'm tired of living....Tired of watching all of my friends...and everyone I love die..."<P><BR>                        "Death comes to all things......."<P>                        "NOT ME!! I have been alive longer then there was time!! I am older then death is! I am sick of this....go away..let me<BR>                        die"<P>                        "Death comes to all things papa, even you some day..me..my brother...my children...someday they wil pass away too.<BR>                        but that is one of the facts of life."<P>                        "What's the point of it all..."<P>                        "To live. To make the most of your existence. Not to throw it away, papa. You loved mom and she loved you. Do you<BR>                        think she would want you to throw your life away?"<P>                        "No..."<P>                        "And in a way shes not gone. Look at me Papa. Didn't you always say that I was the mirror image of mom?"<P>                        Reyas turned back to her and stared. He smiled slighty. "Yes."<P>                        "As long as the family goes on, so will she. We love you Papa, and so does she. We won't leave you and niether will<BR>                        she."<P>                        Reyas smiled through some tears. Dyane kissed Reyas on the forehead. "You need to get some rest Papa." Taking a<BR>                        blanket off the bed, she draped it over him. So he could nap watching the sky, through her mother's favorite window.<BR>                        In a few moments, he was snoring, quietly she picked up the pistol and with one hand crushed it.<BR>                        -------------------------------------<BR>A rumble shook the Jumpboat, waking Reyas from his dream. It was dark and overcast and beginning to storm.<P>                        "How did this cat get in here?" said a voice behind the pilots chair "Shoo!!!"<P>                        "Oh shoo yourself Dirk!"<P>                        "Reyas!?!"<P>                        "Duh"<P>                        "How..nevermind. I don't want to knoww. Where are we?"<P>                        "I can't tell through all of these clouds." A lightning bolt went off brightning the dark craft.<P>                        "Hey there is boat, down there in the water. Not a very big one though."<P>                        Reyas jumped up upon Dirk's shoulders and wapped him on the back of the head. "We are 35 thousand feet in the air!<BR>                        Of course it's tiny!!"<P>                        "OW!"<BR>                        ---------------------------------------------<P>                        "HEY!! I found my hard suit!!" Annie called out across the lab<P>                        "Cool. hey let go!...come on! let go! please..stop.HEY!!! Don't touch that!!! ehehheeAAHHAAHAHAHH!! Stop tickling me!!<BR>                        HAHAHAHAHAHHAAHA"<P>                        "What is going on over there?" Annie peered back over to where Nall was being tickled by the newly freed giggling girl.<P>                        "GET YOUR HANDS OF HIM!!!!" Annie screamed startling both Nall and the girl. The girl scowled at Annie and then stuck<BR>                        her tongue out her. Annie fumed and lunged at the girl, but before she grab hold and start pulling at the girl's hair. Nall<BR>                        jumped inbetween them.<P>                        "Ladies. There is plenty of me to go around, no need to fight over me."<P>                        "FIGHT OVER YOU!!!!!...I AM NOT FIGHTING OVER YOU!!" She screeched. " I am simply trying to help you, by keeping a<BR>                        subversive naked hussy from swaying you"<P>                        The girl, though while not entirely understanding all of Annie's words did catch her tone and direction of sentence. So<BR>                        she clutched Nall closer and stuck her tongue out at Annie. Annie fumed and lunged at the girl again, but was<BR>                        intercepted by Nall again.<P>                        "Ladies! Please let us get out of here first!"<P>                        Annie scowled once again, then turned away and went back to where she was a few moments ago. "That's what I was<BR>                        talking about. I found my hardsuit, it's in this lab...but it's locked" She smiles "not that it is a problem. The wrist<BR>                        transponder is outside though ."<P>                        She holds up a small electronic wristband. <P>                        "How does that help us? Let go! I can't breath..." The girl still holds on tightly<P>                        Annie frowns. "Watch this" She depresses a button on the wristband and her body fades slightly. The dismantled<BR>                        hardsuit on the other side of the glass, disappears. A few seconds , Annie fades back in fully encompassed by her<BR>                        hardsuit.<P>                        "TADA!!!" She giggles and gives Nall the peace symbol.<P>                        "COOL! Solid to Mana conversion!!" Nall wriggles out of the unnamed girl's hug to admire Annie/Aquamarine. The girl<BR>                        scowls as while Nall's back is turned, Annie has the hardsuit face plate retract and she sticks her tonque out at the girl.<P><BR>                        ""You three are terrible."" a voice spoke<P>                        "Who said that?"<BR>                        "Who said that?"<P>                        '"Me, the sword. Atwight. I hate to interrupt this hilarious love triangle, but we should try to get out of here before we<BR>                        are discovered." <P>                        "Atwight is right. Let's go."<BR>                        ------------------------------------<BR>                        "It seems like that ship is our destination. From the size of it, I would say that is the Gunboat Diplomat."<P>                        "How can you tell?"<P>                        "I can see from here that there are over 100 guns on the thing. No other ship in history has that many guns or ever<BR>                        carried such a large array of guns. Even the previous ones held obscene amounts of armaments."<P>                        "I take it you are as old as I am?"<P>                        "Probably older then you can dream. We will be landing in a few minutes, get ready!"<P>                        A large beam of light opens the sky and cuts through the Gunboat Diplomat.<P>                        "HOLY!!!"<P>                        "WHOA!!" They both shout as a shockwave rocks the Jumpboat, as they recover from the jolting. They look back out<BR>                        the window to see the Gunboat Diplomat in two pieces. One smaller piece, the forehalf was already sinking, the larger<BR>                        half was listing about to go under.<P>                        "NALL!!"<BR>                        "TRINI!!!"<P>                        The Jumpboat accelerated and dove toward the sinking battlecruiser.<BR>                        -----------------------------<P>"You know all things considered. That was way too easy." Annie said as they sneaked up onto the main deck.<P>                        "Don't jinx it. All we have to do is make it to that jumpcraft and we are s-"<P>                        The sound of rifles beign ****ed echos in the previously silent night air.<P>                        "FREEZE!!"<P>                        "-afe..."<P>                        "I told you this was to easy..." They raise their arms and turn around to a platoon of armed guards.<P>                        The sound of metal clanking upon the deck comes from behind them. The guards shift their aim to the new presence<BR>                        and then stand down to at-ease posture.<P>                        "Leave us" Calls the deep voice.<P>                        "SIR! YES SIR!!"<P>                        The platoon snaps a salute and vanishes back into the ship. Nall, Annie and the silent girl turn around to face a figure<BR>                        completely covered in jet-black armor. The girl trembled slightly and hid behind Nall.<P>                        "Who are you!"<P>                        "A messenger."<P>                        "What's the message?"<P>                        "Abandon the girl and flee if you wish to see another day. Do not listen her lies about the Void. It must not be freed."<P>                        "And if I choose not to heed this mesage?"<P>                        The man glowed slightly.<P>                        "You die."<P>        