[Atwight]<P>                        Atwight...some how it seems famaliar..I can't put by finger on it..<P>                        [Of course, you don't have any fingers]<P>                        .....Smart alec...<P>                        Reyas switched his concentration back to the trio. "I'm setting the course to Ell-Five, we should be at the stratorbital<BR>                        in about 15 minutes. Good thing too, we only got 16 minutes of fuel."<P>                        The Jumpbaoat flared it's engines to maximum, to make the ascent to Ell-Five, as it ascended, the group made quick<BR>                        patchwork to the hole in the door, so it wouldn't decompress again at the higher altitude of Ell-Five. It wouldn't hold<BR>                        long, being just a plastic sheet, but it would be long enough.<BR>                        -----------------------------------<P>                        Several days later, after lavishly spending Annie's money, Nall's pride and joy was back in complete working order.As<BR>                        they waited for the Flight control in Ell-Five to cycle the Naked Elf to drop station. The band of companions discussed<BR>                        their next destination along with other items.<P>                        "I can't believe, you spent 4 million platinum fixing this piece of junk. Even for a airship, this thing is old! It looks like an<BR>                        old sailing ship with propellers! What a piece of sh-"<P>                        "Don't badmouth my ship!!! It maybe old-fashioned or even an antique maybe, but it is the fastest and most powerful<BR>                        craft in existence. It's my baby." Nall says prodly as he rubs and then hugs main mast of the ship.<P>                        "Hmph..I still think it's a piece of junk.."<P>                        "I'll be more then happy to show you the way out." Nall says pointing to the fact, the Naked Elf had been cycled to the<BR>                        main lock and the ocean and clouds, far far below where just underneath.<P>                        Annie looks over and jumps "AHH! We are high!!Where's the ground!!"<P>                        "About 13 miles down."<P>                        "are you sure this thing works? "<P>                        "Ohh course, my ship is the best-" A small piece of the mast, Nall was leaning against comes off. "...there is.."<P>                        "oh lord.."<P>                        -Attention Vessel 4512 Designation: Naked Elf, please stand by for final cycling and cross lock. Air will be pumped out<BR>                        and mana field will be disengaged in T-minus 4 minutes.-<P>                        "Hey reminds me..Nall this thing is completly open air!!! We are going to suffocate way up here!!"<P>                        "You worry to much Annie, we will be fine. Trust me and trust the Naked elf." Another piece of the mast falls off<P>                        "We're going to die..."<P>                        On a set of boxes, Reyas still in his lower form, sits waiting for the Naked Elf to take off, conversing silently with<BR>                        Atwight.<P>                        [An interesting vessel. Your Grandson seems to have much affinity for it. ]<P>                        Understandable, besides me, this ship is all he has left. All of his family is gone.<P>                        [Dead?]<P>                        Some, some have just vanished...but the main reason he loves this ship so much, is because of the previous owner.<P>                        [Who?]<P>                        His mother, this ship belonged to her. Ruby Tayus, the greatest pirate ever to sail the seas or sky. The Naked Elf was<BR>                        hers, until the was captured..more like betrayed..by my own son, Nall's father, I'm afraid...and executed.<P>                        [Does he know?]<P>                        Not really, he knowss that someone in his mother's crew betrayed her , but not that it was his father. He only knows<BR>                        that Azreal, just got up and left one day, leaving him all alone.<P>                        [So sad..]<P>                        Yes.....but he is happy, he has the Naked Elf and memories of the days when he was young sailing across the sky with<BR>                        his mother. Cannons firing, all that sort of good stuff.<P>                        [Does he aspire to become like her?]<P>                        Not to my knowledge. He just likes to sail the skys and go where ever the wind and the Elf takes him.<P>                        [How romantic]<P>                        Hmm...<P>                        [By the way, back at the Diplomat, it seemed like that attacker knew you. Did you know him?]<P>                        Yes...or at least I thought I did...I really don't understand him any more...and honestly I am too tired to try. I am<BR>                        getting very old.<P>                        [Bah, you are dragon. ageless, always in the prime of youth. Quite helpful in the wee hours don't you think?]<P>                        And I thought I was lecherous. Speaking of dragons, why is it I feel somethng famaliar from you? It's almost<BR>                        draconion..faint..but draconion.<P>                        [You just haven't had a female companion in while that's all. Prime of youth getting up again. Shamelessly bad pun<BR>                        intended]<P>                        Bah!<P>                        Theiir silent conversation, was broken as Nall signaled to everyone to come together to discuss their next plan of<BR>                        action. As he did so, Lilith began to talk, in fact the most she had said in the entire time they had known her.<P>                        "We must free Void, for all of...Nor...nor...this world. The ony way to do that, is to find the 5 keys, to Void. I only know<BR>                        of two. One is on Veeshan...we are not strong enough to fight her...., the second is in Fear."<P>                        Reyas shuddered at the thought of his fomer home 500 years ago, but gritted his teeth and entered the conversation.<P>                        "If we have to get something from the Plane of Fear..more then likely from Cazic-Thule. Then the best place to try<BR>                        would, be through his strongest disciples. There is only one place where that can be."<P>                        "Palsa" They all said together.<P>                        Dirk who was up and around, but not very active and not in the huddle,was just looking over the side rail, over heard<BR>                        the destination.<P>                        Palsa.....Maxim.....If he couldn't Trini back at the moment, then at least he could get Maxim..He held out his hand, and<BR>                        began to think about the chance to finally get revenge, his hand ignited into flames.<P>                        "Fire it up." He laughed.<P>                        -Naked Elf, cross lock is complete, releasing main clamps. Air evac wil began in T-minus 30 seconds. Point of No return<BR>                        has been passed, release system can not be overrided.-<P><BR>                        "Nall, are you sure this piece of junk will fly?'<P>                        "Yes,positive. And besides it's a litte late now for doubts" He pointed upward, the massive stratorbital Ell-Five loomed<BR>                        above them, the open sky to their left, right and bottom.<P>                        (Music Cue The Journey Begins : Final Fantasy 2 (American Numbering) )<P>                        The Naked Elf shuddered as it's old fashioned Gnomish clockwork engines began to start. The props in the fore and and<BR>                        aft of the ship began to whirl. Amazingly, the wind did not start to pick up as expected on the deck. The props<BR>                        chopped the air, rapidly gaining speed, and in a few sort moments, became almost invisible rotating at such a high<BR>                        speed.<P>                        -Air evac complete, mana field disabled. Cross-Locks will disengage in 5 seconds....4.....3...2......Elevator going<BR>                        down....1.-<P>                        The locks snapped off the Elf, it lurched slightly, but quickly righted and began to gently sail from underneath the<BR>                        immense Stratorbital. It movedd across the sky majestically, and began a gentle turn to the SouthWest...to Odus.<BR>                        --------------------------------------<P><BR>                        The man ran ad ran. He was all that was left, al that was left of the news crew. They had come to fin out about the<BR>                        disappearance of the some of the well known students of Palsa. Students, that mysteriously vanished after, joining<BR>                        some kindof cult. a cult that taught use of magicks and sorcerorcy. Ad other outdated practices, why any one would<BR>                        want to learn about mana , sorcery and demons was beyond him..or at least was 15 minutes ago. No he understood,<BR>                        his current state was a testament to that, the blood running down his face, stinging his eyes, the burns on his arms,<BR>                        his urine soaked pants. now he understood...not that it would do him any good.<P>                        He ran and ran, the door to end of the cult hall was almost in reach, he could see teh city lights, but he fell, a sharp<BR>                        pain had ripped through his right arm..or at least where there used to be a arm.<P>                        He screamed and screamed hoping some one would hear him..come save him and he was lucky some one did hear him.<BR>                        The most of the city did, and some one did come for him, but not to save him.<P>                        Flames seemed to seep from everywhere,from every crevice in the room, but amazingly, though the flames burned<BR>                        brightly,t he shadows did receed, but he couldn't be amzedby this he was too terrified. The flames circled around him,<BR>                        he could feel the awesome heat from it, the flames began to consolidate an in a moment, a fgure emrged out of the<BR>                        flames. Him....Maxim. the leader of the cult...the teacher of the old ways, the old ways of the shadows and<BR>                        Cazic-Thule.<P>                        Maxim began to speak in that cold distant voice. "You droppd this" His arm fell into his lap. He wanted to scream, but<BR>                        for some reason he was just too scared.Maxim laughe, it echoing monsteriously in the huge room. Chains leapt out of<BR>                        the darkness , encompassing the man by his arm and legs, and righted him.<P>                        "Run.." The man was scared and did not comply. "RUN!!!!' A chain shed across the mman's chest biting deep into his<BR>                        flesh, the man turned and ran as fast he could. As ran and ran, closer and closer to the exit, he thought he saw the<BR>                        shadows move. he got closer, they moved again, he began to push harder, trying to gain more speed, but then he<BR>                        heard it. Hard breathing, then the sounds of paws slapping across the ground. it was getting closer..closer, it was<BR>                        getting cold. He screamed again, as something bit into his right legs, blood streamed, he felt him self being hoisted in<BR>                        the air and flung around like a doll. it shook him again and again, and eventually his leg came off. he skided across te<BR>                        grund, blood pouring, and he saw it. The shadows themselves where his assailant, the shadows had teeth, the shadows<BR>                        where getting closer. The shadows began ripping at his chest, she screamed and screamed for a long time and<BR>                        eventually he stopped and the light began to fde from his eyes, but the ripping continued for a long time<P><BR>                        As the slaughter contnued, Maxim in the center of room, assumed a lotus posiotn and smiled a the sight.<P>                        "Enjoy your meal, Pain."<P>                        And with one exhaling, his body went cold as death, his surrondings began to disappear and were replaced, by the<BR>                        Plane of Fear.<P>                        "You have done well, Maxim. For you service, I hav a reward for you."<P>                        "Him?"<P>                        "No, but this will bring him. Find the Maelstrom gate, and destroy Errolisi like you did Tunare."<P>                        "It will be done."<P>                        Maxim began a different comune, a one of rememberance. Memories began to pass over him until he came to the one of<BR>                        most use andpleasure. The army of Thule, the army of darkness, and the completle conquering of the Plane of Growth.<BR>                        ---------------------<BR>                        End of This Chapter<BR>                        ---------------------<P>                        Sneak Peek of Chapter 4 Tides of Darkness<BR>                        --------------------------<BR>(one Chapter left  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> This is long aint it?)
