Because Ch.5 is taking far longer then I orginally thought and I am a nice guy (stop laughing! ), here is what I am             going to do. I am going to break Ch.5 into parts!(  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"> I am an evil nice guy aren't I? ^-^) So here is what you have all           been waiting for!! pt.1!!!<BR>--------------------<BR>Ch.5 Blood Moon<BR>--------------------<P>----------------<BR>Loc Stamp: Palsian Air Force(P.A.F.) DropShip &lt;i&gt;Flying Nerf Stick&lt;/i&gt;<BR>ETA to LZ Minotaur: 7 minutes<BR>----------------<P>The Lieutenant walked up the ranks making a last inspection, shaking his head in disgust at the new recruits that were added to reinforce the Strikers.<P>"What a bunch of apes…to think this sorry bunch had to be dropped on me.....Maybe I should have Ori turn this bucket around back to Palsa."<P>"Really Lieutenant? Cool!"<P>"Shaddap Hienes. You aren't that lucky. It's slackers like you that are a detriment to the corp. I bet you don't even know the operation."<P>"...You would be correct, Sir!"<P>The Lieutenant shook his head again. "Sarge. Educate them."<P>"Yes, Sir. This is a joint operation to reclaim the accursed continent back, after 500 years of infection by the Dread King. At Zero 9 hundred hours this morning, the Flagship <I>Limiting Factor</I> and the Heavy Gunships <I>Gunsmoke</I> and <I>Hell's Fury</I> commenced bombardment of a 3 mile radial section of terrain near the ButcherBlock Mountains. Approximately, where the ancient seaport once was. By now that area is one large patch of glass. At exactly thirteen hundred hours, we will be going in with first wave. That means more dead for us to rest. Not a problem for the Strykers! Am I right!?!"<P>The soldiers let out cry of affirmation. The Sergeant smiled.<P>" At 15 hundred hours we are scheduled to be in the Greater Faydark. I expect you to do better! I want you in Steamfront by then!  Do you get me!"<P>"WE GET YOU SIR!!"<P>" At that time, En-Gen fast carrier &lt;i&gt; Dew Fray&lt;/i&gt; will rendezvous with us and drop off a contingent of En-Gen Special Forces. We will recall into the Dew Fray and fall back at the HQ set up in the LZ by the En-Gen engineering corp.  At seventeen hundred Faydwer will be ours, not withstanding a few pockets of further resistance. At eighteen hundred, we will be on every news cast on the planet boys. HOO-AH!"<P>"HOO-AH!" Echoed the soldiers.<P>"I hate to interrupt the testosterone flow guys, but LZ Minotaur is dead ahead. 3 minutes till drop. On the ready line!" Ori cut in over the intercom<P>"On the ready line!! Sound off! One! ...Two!!" He called out as the soldiers got up from their seats, sealing their armor and arming weapon systems.<P>Ori opened the comm again. "LZ in 2 minutes and 30 seconds. Opening Doors. Looking good boys!"<P>The sleek dropship's wings swung out from it's tucked position, instantly creating massive drag bringing the craft out of super sonic. As the ocean rapidly diminished giving way to glassy beachhead, the troops of Synwol's Strykers looked in awe at the combined might of the world's mightiest nation and the world's most powerful corporation. Palsa and En-Gen working together in one common goal, the reclamation of the accursed continent...Faydwer.<BR>----------------------------<BR>				   <BR>Dirk leaned against the rail as the Naked Elf descended from the skies. He flinched slightly when he rubbed the bandage on his forehead, where Nall had whacked him with a brick, when he found the hole in the Naked Elf punched into existence by Dirk. He grumbled slightly about it, then laughed as Reyas came bounding out of the lower deck closely pursued by a  hailstorm of objects and clothing.<P>"AND STAY OUT OF MY ROOM!!!!" screeched Annie<P>Reyas massaged his own fuzzy head and then opened his wings and flew up to the helm.  Nall stood at the helm, with a smile on his face 20 miles wide. He had his ship working once again, the wind in his face, a cadre of new friends, and almost as important as the Naked Elf working again......two beautiful girls all for him! His smile grew wider. Sounds of paws hitting the deck, broke him out of his daydream..<P>"Hey Grandpa...what was Annie screaming about?"<P>"Something about her clothes."<P>"Oh."<P>".....or lack of..." he mumbled...<P>"huh?"<P>"Nothing. When will we be setting down?"<P>"About an hour , give or take a few minutes depending on the wind."<P>"Sounds good……"<P>"Something bothering you Grandpa?"<P>"No…well a little…I just have this feeling something big is going to happen...probably just those batwing crunchies I had last night."<BR>--------------------<BR>The Last Chance bar was finally kicking into gear, as the large glass of mead where being passed around. Nosrac Yald the owner of the pub, stepped up to the mic to introduce the first band of the night, much to the crowds delight, the band was one of most popular in all of Norrath.<P>"WELLCOME EVEYWON! I'M GWAD TO SEE YA HERE!!!"<P>The crowd being that it had been waiting a very long time was not a good reception for the poor owner and began to throw things at him while chanting "WE WANT THE BAND! WE WANT THE BAND!!"<P>"AWIGHT! AWIGHT! HERS DA BAND!! ANGEL DUST!!!"<P>The club immediately went black and the battered owner dashed off the stage dodging a few more pieces of food and one chair. A few moments ticked by and then the sounds of drums drifted through the air, the crowd began to stir. A guitar riff joined the drums, the crowd began to cheer. <P>(Music Cue: Control (Apocalypse Remix) by Poe)<P>Spotlights crawled across the rising stage curtain and cast their light on the star. Her wings at first to the audience, this lovely half breed human/Aviak an 'Angel' was at the top of the music scene. The crowd went wild as Cassandra tapped her foot to the beat for a few moments and then as she began to sing, the crowd went insane.<P>&lt;marquee&gt;"Don't you mess with a little girl's dream, 'Cause she's liable to grow up mean. Surprised you to find that I'm laughing? You thought that you'd find me in tears, You thought I'd be crawling the walls, Like a tiny mosquito and trembling in fear, Well you may be king for the moment, But I am a queen understand, And I've got your pawns and your bishops, And castles, All inside the palm of my hand,  While you were looking the other way, While you had your eyes closed, While you were licking your lips, 'Cause I was miserable, While you were selling your soul ,While you were tearing a hole in me…."&lt;/marquee&gt;<P>-----------------<P>Scott and Eris ran and ran as fast as they could, they had managed to dodge the troops twice already, but the chance of doing again where slim, but they knew if they could get to the city of Palsa they would be safe...for a while.<P>After running for a long time and running past old ruins, they finally stopped to rest in the icy tundra at the foot of the Stonebrunt Mountains. They only had a bit of traveling to do but it was mostly uphill, the sprawling city of Palsa was at the base of Mount Claw, several miles away upward.  <P>Eris plopped down on top of rock and sighed heavily, her breath hanging in the frigid air. Scott preferred to stand and just gaze at the majesty of this frozen tundra. He was concerned about Eris, though the troopers for the first part of their flight had chased them, the last hour or so they had been alone. Something was troubling her, but he couldn't figure it out and was unsure about how to ask...she seemed too reserved all of a sudden.<P>He took a deep breath and then turned to face her. "Eris, is the-"<P>"There they are!!! Squad attack!"<P>"****!!" As Scoot whipped back around to face the troopers he caught a glimpse of their armor… Ghost's …their old unit…obviously reinforced with new Ghosts…but still… their former unit.<P>"I suggest you surrender Scott. Dead or alive you're coming with us!"<P>That voice…His former C.O...he never really liked him...oh well...time for payback. The Despair began to glow as it sensed the coming fight. Scott charged forward..	<BR>(End Music-Cue)<BR>---------------------<BR>"Lock and Load Boys!!!" Called Ori "Missiles away! Jump 10 after impact!!!"<P>(Music Cue:Woohoo- Starship Troopers Soundtrack)<P>As the swift dropship skimmed across the earth, four missiles leapt from it's belly. They cut out and slammed into an encroaching line of Fallen. The Fallen where immediately incinerated by the star hot atomic warheads, had it not been for the En-Gen patented mana buffers inside the missiles, they would have gone critical mass and released a devastating far reaching explosion and expelled tons of radiation. But these only glassed 100 meters each and with no more rad then a microwave.<P>The Sarge counted ticks in his head till ten and then cried out "LET's GO STRIKERS!!!" , the Strikers made a loud jarring War cry and stepped out of the dropship. Each one only had to fall about 70 feet and the majority of the velocity from the ship and the fall was cut by light expenditures of jump juice, the remaining Delta Vee was taken in the armor, smoothly like all the Strykers were trained to do.<P>"Form up, sweeping pattern Romengo. Demurs take the point. Lets show these dead some rest!!" the Sarge's orders came through in each of their helmets.<P>The familiar staccato of gunfire disrupted the horrendous moans of the dead...or the Fallen as the military slang goes. For the first time in 500 years, life was beating back death.<BR>(End Music Cue)<BR>----------------------<BR>The crowd was pumped up Angel Dust's performance, it was no wonder why they where the best. The unique sound, the lyrics, Cassandra's long flowing hair with it's streaks of silver and blue and of course her form-fitting revealing outfits. The crowd began to scream as the band geared up for their next song.<P>(Music Cue: "Youth of the Nation" by P.O.D)<P>&lt;marquee&gt; "Last day of the rest of my life , I wish I would've known, Cause I didn't kiss my mama goodbye, I didn't tell her that I loved her and how much I care, Or thank my pops for all the talks, And all the wisdom he shared, Unaware, I just did what I always do, Everyday, the same routine, Before I skate off to school, But who knew that this day wasn't like the rest, Instead of taking a test, I took two to the chest, Call me blind, but I didn't see it coming,  Everybody was running, But I couldn't hear nothing, Except gun blasts, it happened so fast, I don't really know this kid ,Even though I sit by him in class, Maybe this kid was reaching out for love, or maybe for a moment, He forgot who he was, Or maybe this kid just wanted to be hugged,         Whatever it was, I know it's because &lt;/marquee&gt;<P>                                             <BR>  As she got to the chorus, the crowd sang with her.                        <P><BR>&lt;marquee&gt;  We are, We are, the youth of the nation! We are, We are, the youth of the nation! &lt;/marquee&gt;<P>-------------------------<P>"Uh-oh. Knew we shouldn't have got those cheap ones back at Ell-Five"<P>"What is it Nall?"<P>"…Two of the props just died."<P>"!!!!!! I didn't do it!!"<P>"I didn't say you did!!! But if another prop goes…uh-oh…"<P>Two of the remaining three propellers on the Nekkid Elf die and the troubled ship begins a rapid descent. Luckily the airship had already reached Odus, but unfortunately with the problems, they wouldn't be able to land at the Skyport in Palsa. They would have to crash land in the near by Stonebrunt Mountains.<BR>------------------<P>The battle raged between the 2 former ghosts and their old unit. Aided by their new found gifts, they where able to hold their own, unfortunately their long journey was taking it's toll upon them and they couldn't best the Ghost units. As things seemed their darkest, it became literally quite darker.<P>Both groups noticed the larger shadow being cast upon them and the looked up toward the sun too see a very large ship blocking out the light…making a very uncoordinated fall to the ground…as the groups stared slack jawed forgetting about the fight, they soon noticed the ship was getting bigger and closer…to them.<P>"It's going to crash land here!!!!" Both Scott and his former C.O called out.<P>Taking advantage of the moment, Eris to her surprise cast an ancient magic, the Ghost unit's feet sank deep into the earth with out further delay she grabbed a slack-jawed Scott and dragged him away from the area. A few moments later the Nekkid Elf slammed into the mountain range into what could have been thought as a minor earthquake, it slid across the icy tundra tearing up the landscape and soon came to a rest.<P>As time past, a cargo door in the back of the Elf opened and Nall's cadre stumbled out, obviously shaken up by the crash… except for Nall and Annie.<P>(End Music cue)<P>"WHAT KIND OF PILOTING DO YOU CALL THAT!?!"<P>"YOU'RE ALIVE, AREN'T YOU?!! I told you we shouldn't have skimped on those gears! But nooooo, Miss CopperPinch had to get the cheap gears! "What harm could it do Nall, gears are all the same Nall!"<P>He glowered at her for a minute and then walked around to survey the ship. For the most part, the Elf was unharmed aside from some red marks on the keel and some large paint scratches that brought Nall to tears. "My poor baby…don't you worry, Nall will fix you right up, don't you worry."<P>Lilith wandered over to Nall to comfort him, Reyas preferred just to wander around with Dirk to survey the area, leaving Annie alone by herself.<P>"Do you have to sit on my head?"<P>"Yes, it's nice and warm up here."<P>"…Infernal- hmmm. Looks like we have company."<P>As Scott and Eris slowly came into view, a chill ran through Dirk's spine. He could feel two underlying presences with these two.<P><I>It's them again. </I> Dirk's hand went to his pistol and he examined the two young soldiers closer.<P>He's carrying the Despair...and why do I feel Tunare's aura emanating from the girl?<P>The boy wielding the Despair held it at ready unsure what to make of the pale-skinned elf...with the winged cat on his head. He seemed almost ready to attack, but the girl put her hand on his shoulder relaxing him. Somehow she seemed to recognize Dirk, even though she hadn't exactly had time for introductions. She walked up to Dirk and introduced herself.<P>"It's us again."<P>Dirk hesitated. "I'm glad you're ok, but….are you?"<P>"I'm sorry for being so hesitant with you, but we have been running for our lives for some time, but we do owe you our lives. Your ship saved us from being captured by En-Gen."<P>"En-Gen again…they are always up to something…Well any way, My name is Dirk Lunas and this infernal cat who won't get off my head is Reyas." Dirk made an ineffectual attempt to knock Reyas off.<P>"Hi!" Reyas chimed in<P>"He can speak?"<P>"Yes I can!" And with that Reyas hopped off Dirk's head and into Eris's arms. "Let's head back to the ship so we can introduce you to the rest of our group. We were heading to Palsa until the ship broke down. "<P>"Fate seems to have brought us together then, we where also heading to Palsa"<P>"So it seems, my you're nice and warm… Hey Dirk! The ship is this way!"<P>"I have other things to attend to, once I am done, maybe we'll meet again." Dirk called back as he trudged up the mountain, leaving the Elf and the group behind.<P><I> Here I come...Maxim.</I><P>-------------------------------<BR>Several hours later, Nall and his companions made there way into the shining city of Palsa. Each of them with various goals in mind, Annie and Scott where sent to get gears for the Elf...with specific instructions to get the good ones this time. Lilith, who was goggle eyed at the majesty of this place, went out exploring, while Eris, Reyas and Nall were supposed to have been getting info about the temple of Cazic-Thule, being that it wasn't one of things generally talked about in a city like this, but instead they went to bar or more accurately Nall went to a bar to console his sorrows about his yet again damaged Elf dragging the other two with him. It just so happens that the bar he went to, was The Last Chance.<P>It had quieted down a bit in the Last Chance, since the band had taken a break. So Nall was able to get a few rounds of med at the table in front of the stage. After his 7th or 8th round, the lights went out and the spotlights shined on the curtain and the owner shouted through the loudspeakers to pump the crowd up again<P>"HEWWO EVEHONE!! WETS GWIVE A WROUND OF APWAUSE AS OUR BAND COMES BWACK ON! GWIVE IT UP FWOR ANGEL DUST!!!!"<P>Nall and Reyas froze when the owner said the band name. The band behind the curtain began to play and the crowd began to go wild.<P>(Music Cue: "Get the Party Started' by Pink)<P>&lt;marquee&gt; I'm comin up so you better get this party started, I'm comin up so you better get this party started! Get this party started on a Saturday night, Everybody's waiting for me to arrive, Sending out the message to all of my friends, We'll be looking flashy in my Gnomecedes Benz,  I got lots of style check my platinum diamond rings, I can go for miles if you know what I mean, I'm coming up so you better get this party started!!!&lt;/marquee&gt;<P>The curtain slowly rose revealing the band on the chorus , revealing Cassandra with her back to the audience, she turned to face the cheering crowd and the last line of the chorus.<P>"I'm comin up so you better get this party started!!!" And at that moment she noticed Nall sitting in the front row.<P>"YOU!" and with that she gave the audience a puzzle to figure out and something to really scream about. She pulled two semi-auto Gnome and Becker pistols out of her skin- tight outfit and opened fire on Nall.<P>-----------------------------------<P><BR>Dirk was in a curious state both excited yet enraged about the coming moments. Revenge was at hand. Maxim would pay...preferably screaming.<P>As he entered the dark hall of the Temple of Cazic-Thule, several initiates began protesting and made to oust him. <P>"Begone Elf! Visiting ours are over, come back tomorrow!"<P>Dirk smiled and twirled the pointer finger on his right hand and spoke in a sing-song voice "Fiiiirrre" His hand ignited into night-dark flames.<P>The lowly initiates where startled by this and scampered away.<P>Dirk chuckled "Mom always said I hand a radiant personality...heh" he proceeded inward unobstructed, but he quickly grew agitated as Maxim was no where to be found.<P>"MAXIM!!! I know you are here!!! Come out and face me!!!!" Nothing happened, no Maxim. "Fine! Then I will tear this place apart! DEVIL FLARE!!!" The ground around Dirk ignited in black flames and everything within a 15-foot radius was destroyed. That got a response.<P>Fluid, red tendrils of fire crept out of the darkness, flowed around the majestic pillars and idols of Cazic-Thule, all conglomerating in front of Dirk. In a few moments the fires gave away to the form of Maxim. Though he did show it, somehow this Erudite gave Dirk chills...except for the Dread King, he had never felt any one so in touch with and in control of death, but he pushed those thoughts out of his mind, he was here for one purpose.<P>Maxim breathed shallowly, it hung in the piercing cold air for a long time undisturbed...until a shadow chain shot of the darkness.<BR>--------------------------<P>"Ahh....Shamus! Good to see you! Things are going so splendidly. Finally after all this preparation Faydwer will be free! And best of all the world will finally show us the respect we deserve! Truly a great day!"<P>"..."<P>"What is wrong?"<P>"I'm afraid it maybe a while before we can celebrate sir. Things are not going well from the prelims. Resistance is stronger then even the most conservative estimates. The forces are not only encountering 10 times-"<P>"10 TIMES?"<P>"Yes sir..10 times the original Fallen estimates...they are also encountering Fallen types never seen before...races, beasts until know never known to be in existence…The Palsian forces are being decimated. I doubt they will be able to make it to the Waypoints, which will multiply the task load of our Ghosts exponentially. Sir, you know I am the greatest proponent of the Ghosts, but I don't think even they can handle this...and it's only going to get worse...I'm afraid the Palsian government, didn't equip their troops with the Dead man switches."<P>"WHAT!!!"<P>"Yes...they felt it was excessive and wasteful of lives to equip them with the explosives in case of turning. If...no when the Palsian troops die, they are going to be turned and start fighting back with our own equipment...Sir...we may have to consider...aborting and blasting Faydwer from Stratorbit...unless we get a miracle, I believe Faydwer will never be released, glassing the accursed continent would be the only sure way preventing Fallen spread."<P>The Overseer, stared forlornly at his desk...what to do. So much was invested in this...all the technology and might of the world was behind this...how could they be beaten...The people of Odus beat the Dread King before with only swords and arrows...we have bombs, guns, superior training. It was not possible...but wait...he knew like Shamus...or perhaps even better then Shamus the awesome power of the Ghosts. Though their burden would be many times heavier...they could free Faydwer.<P>The Overseer looked back up to Shamus. "No, revise the plan to accommodate the failures of Palsian troops. Reroute the Ghosts and deploy them. They can carve through them, also draw up a plan to supplement the Beachhead...even if this goes sour we are going to maintain a forward base on Faydwer. It belongs to us and we are going to reclaim it...but you are right...even our Ghosts will need help...Patch me through to Deep Star Six"<BR>-----------------------
</FONT>
