<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
----------------------- <BR>                        The two battled on and on Dirk dodged wave after wave of chain barrages, he tried as hard as he<BR>                        could to manage against this incredible onslaught....and ten it happened…he saw it! There it was shining<BR>                        like beacon...an open place to strike in Maxim's barrage. He seized the moment, chains barely missing<BR>                        him, his gauntlet claw extended and dug into Maxim's neck and out the other side. <P>                        "This is for Jesi! DEVIL FLARE!!" Maxim was consumed by the dark flames and incinerated. AS the<BR>                        magical flow, began to ebb Dirk collapsed panting, the battle had tired him...but at last...he avenged<BR>                        Jesi...Maxim was gone...forever. As he began to settle into the Euphoria of that thought, something<BR>                        dashed in his peripheral vision. He turned to the movement, to see a Shadow beast lunging at him, it's<BR>                        teeth bared. It was too quick there was nothing he could do...this was it... <P>                        Or so he thought, the beast growled slightly as it bounced off an invisible barrier. The beast clawed at<BR>                        the barrier, but was unable to get past it. It growled once again and faded into the darkness. As it<BR>                        disappeared, Dirk heard the sounds of footsteps behind him, he turned to the sounds. <P>                        "You!" <P>                        "Is that any way to talk to the person that saved your life?" Rashan replied in that disturbing overlapping<BR>                        voice. <P>                        "Should I be thankful? The first we met, you helped the kidnapping of my daughter and the last time<BR>                        you tried to turn me into flambé!" <P>                        "Hmm. I can always allow Maxim to kill you if you would like" Rashan said motioning to the shadows<BR>                        behind Dirk <P>                        "Maxim's dead." Dirk stated proudly as he got to his feet <P>                        "So you think Black Elf, but unfortunately for you Hell Lords…even undeserving ones are far more<BR>                        durable then you would think. Maxim is still quite alive, the fact that I just stopped his familiar from<BR>                        tearing you apart is proof of that." <P>                        "A Shadow beast...A familiar?" <P>                        "Yes, it is interesting how Thule has been dolling out familiars for his knights...a shadow beast here, a<BR>                        dragon there. Heh…well. I guess it isn't amusing to one such as yourself." <P>                        Rashan vanished. <P>                        "Humph, so why do I have the honor of your presence freak?" Dirk called out as he spun around<BR>                        looking for Rashan. It took a moment but he found Rashan standing on top of a large idol of<BR>                        Cazic-Thule<P>                        "Tsk, tsk Dirk. There is no need for name calling. I have come here, to help you." <P>                        "Help me! Hah! I don't see how you can be of any help to me!" <P>                        "Hmm maybe not, but at least do me the courtesy of hearing me out for saving your life. I think you may<BR>                        like my proposition." <P>                        "Hah, I doubt it, but please go on" He said putting as much contempt he could in his voice. <P>                        "What I wish from you, is to stop your companions from retrieving the Void keys. That is all." <P>                        "This helps me how?" <P>                        "In exchange for keeping them from retrieving the keys, I will tell you how to kill Maxim." <P>                        "No deal! I can kill him on my own!" <P>                        "Oh really?" Rashan vanished again and the shadow beast reappeared charging Dirk, with the barrier<BR>                        gone it crashed right into Dirk spilling him on the floor. The foul thing pounced on top of Dirk and sank<BR>                        it's teeth into his shoulder but before it could do anymore damage, it began to howl in pain and quickly<BR>                        receded back into the darkness. <P>                        Rashan appeared above Dirk looking down on the batter elf. <P>                        "I thought you said you could handle Maxim?" <P>                        "Yes.....I know…I said Maxim...I said nothing about Shadow beasts......" <P>                        Rashan laughed slightly, but sobered quickly. Dirk got back onto his feet and stood face to face with<BR>                        Rashan. <P>                        "Still no deal…I want Maxim dead, yes...but he is only luxury that presented himself.." <P>                        "I see. I know what you want" <P>                        "Do you?" <P>                        "Trini." <P>                        "Yes, give me back my daughter and I will stop Lilith and Nall from acquiring the keys...I don't care<BR>                        about them or you for that matter. Trini is all that matters." <P>                        Rashan softly laughed again <P>                        "You care much the child, even though she is not truly yours...Most admirable Dirk." <P>                        Dirk's face contorted with shock. "What do you mean?" <P>                        "Hehe.." Rashan vanished again. <P>                        "DAMN IT COME BACK HERE!!!!" <P>                        Rashan began to speak again from behind Dirk. "Trini is not truly your daughter, being an elf yourself<BR>                        you should know that elven pregnancies can vary wildly, from say 4 months or several years." <P>                        Dirk went pale...no this couldn't be... Elven pregnancies could last a long time...that could mean...that<BR>                        Jesi could have been pregnant when she returned back to Faydwer with him... making.. <P>                        "....Maxim is?" <P>                        "Yes and no." <P>                        "What do you mean?" <P>                        "In actuality, Void is more of the 'father' then either of you, but I'll explain that in a moment. Suffice it to<BR>                        say, both You and Maxim are Trini's father." <P>                        "That...just can't be! That's…That's-" <P>                        "Impossible" Rashan said finishing Dirk's sentence. "Nothing is impossible , especially when you are so<BR>                        close to Void's influence." <P>                        "Explain!" <P>                        "Kymura...I'm sorry Tunare, never really told you why she wanted you to guard her temple in Faydwer<BR>                        did she?...Well, I am not surprised by that, but hadn't you ever wondered about the barrier surrounding<BR>                        the temple?" <P>                        "Yes, but I always thought it was the last of her powers." <P>                        "In a way it was, you see Tunare did not want Void to be released, so she asked you to guard her<BR>                        Void key, but thing is you are just a mortal after all, so despite the great trust she placed in you, she did<BR>                        not completely do so. So with her dying breath and amplifying it through the power of the key she<BR>                        created the barrier around the temple. You see the key is the strength and weakness of the barrier and<BR>                        your promise to Tunare." <P>                        "Continue" <P>                        "While the key would ensure that the Dread King or any other evil influence would penetrate to steal it,<BR>                        it being a part of the Void, could radiate Void's influence, namely your beloved and 'faithful' Jesi. Void<BR>                        poisoned her mind to seek out some one as strong or stronger then you and conceive a child. With this<BR>                        completed, she returned to you and Void then combined a part of you into the child with in her.<BR>                        Creating Trini for Void's purposes, namely to become a host." <P>                        "A host? For what or whom!" <P>                        "You already know, you just aren't using your head." <P>                        Dirk was still numb from all this information that was being dumped on him...he couldn't think....then it<BR>                        hit him. <P>                        "My corporeal form may be destroyed....but I will always return...but even so....my new form....will<BR>                        be able to contain...all of my power......not just a token...like Veeshan's gift......"<P>                        "Soon.....the child's soul and corporeal bind...will belong...to me...just ....as the soul and corporeal bind<BR>                        of the..... mother belongs to Palsa......" <P>                        "Soon...you will see.....Dirk........Lunas......." <P>                        "NO!!!" Dirk leapt at Rashan, unable to contain his anger, but he was caught by an unseen force that<BR>                        clamped on his neck and began to tighten. <P>                        "Do try to keep your temper under control Dirk, I would hate to see anything unfortunate happen to<BR>                        you." <P>                        The force released Dirk and he crashed to the ground. <P>                        "...the dread King...my Trini…was created...for the Dread King?" <P>                        "Yes. Like all things, Void hates imprisonment. So Void will stop at nothing to be free, whether it be<BR>                        persuading combinate creatures such as Lilith or beings such as the Dread King. It makes no difference<BR>                        how it is done, just as long as Void is freed. So in a way you should thank me Lunas." <P>                        "Thank you!?!" <P>                        "Right now, your child is safe and protected and in excellent hands. In fact, as of right now, she is<BR>                        probably playing some sort of Video entertainment with her favorite Uncle…or as you know him, the<BR>                        Overseer of En-Gen." <P>                        "AAAAAAH!!!" Dirk leapt again at Rashan, but again the same force caught him and clamped down,<BR>                        this time though it slammed into the ground knocking the wind of him. <P>                        "Take my advice Dirk, do not try that again. You have neither the skill nor the power to harm me." <P>                        The force let go of Dirk and he gasped for breath. <P>                        "So, if I promise to tell you how to kill Maxim and allow you to see your Daughter, will you stop your<BR>                        companions?" <P>                        "...What if I refuse?" <P>                        "I will find some other means of stopping them, most likely it will be forceful but oh well, and you will<BR>                        never be able to kill Maxim or find out where your daughter is. Well, think about Dirk, the choice is<BR>                        yours." <P>                        Rashan vanished again and now devastated emotionally and to a lesser extent, physically Dirk cried<BR>                        unsure of what else to do.<P>                        ---------------------<BR>                        End of Part 1. Part 2 coming soon to a CR near you 8)
</FONT>
